trend_summary: Across the series, the inner grid gradually fills, industrial parcels redevelop into mixed commercial blocks, and river-edge brownfields green into parkland. Built form spreads only slightly outward; most growth is vertical or infill, keeping the footprint stable but roof coverage higher.
notable_changes: Vacant lots within the downtown grid replaced by new rooftops, raising overall building density.
South-west industrial zone near the runway gains additional warehouses and logistics buildings.
Riverfront strip transitions from disused land to landscaped green space and trails.
Highway interchange sees added ramps and wider lanes, improving regional access.
Minor runway extension and new taxiways indicate airport capacity upgrades.
